messages.message:
Actively investigating the following, apologies in advance for any delays in getting PRs merged. I’d like to do more digging before I restart PreProd Jenkins, but will time-box it to the next 45 minutes. :+1:
https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C035SLYCJ9X/p1694006976117379

*Heads up* that you might see your PR merge check jobs fail on “container name exists” errors - job resumption is not always the smoothest of things across a restart. If you see this, just rerun, the job has an unconditional post-stage to cleanup whatever container it was using (or trying to use, as the case may be)
